(Translated by Google) Today I casually tried to place an order to pick up and the person who answered the phone, after taking my order, told me that I had to cancel it because it exceeded $ 50.00, and I had to pay for it in advance. We have been customers of this restaurant for years, it is the first time that I have placed an order to be picked up and paid for at the same time, in fact my son was on his way to pick it up and he wanted to pay for it. The person who attended me said his name was Juan Sebastian, I asked him about the owner or the manager and he denied them, I had given him my phone number so that he could verify that we are clients for a long time, but he still refused. This place has been one of our favorites since it opened, I even think it was previously called primarepa and we were also its customers. I know that businesses are currently going through very difficult times, and that many rules have changed as a result of the situation, but for that reason we should not close our ears and common sense and harm or to some extent mistreat loyal customers. It is a shame not to have been able to enjoy your delicious food and in turn you lose a client.  (Original) Hoy casualmente trate de poner una orden para recojer y la persona que contesto el telefono, despues de haber tomado mi orden, me dijo que tenia que cancelarla porque excedia los $50.00, y tenia que pagarla por adelantado. Somos clientes de este restaurante por anos, es la primera vez que pongo una order para ser recojida y pagada al mismo tiempo, de hecho mi hijo estaba en camino para recojerla y el queria pagarla. La persona que me atendio dijo llamarse Juan Sebastian, le pregunte por el dueno o el manager y me los nego, yo le habia dado mi # de telefono para que comprobara que somos clientes por mucho tiempo, pero igual se nego. Este lugar a sido uno de nuestros favoritos desde que abrio, incluso creo que anteriormente era llamado primarepa y tambien eramos sus clientes. yo se que actualmente los negocios estan pasando por momentos muy dificiles, y que han cambiado muchas reglas producto de la situacion, pero no por eso debemos de cerrar los oidos y el sentido comun y perjudicar o hasta cierto punto maltratar a clientes fieles. Es una pena no haber podido disfrutar de su rica comida y a su vez ustedes perder un cliente.
